text: Jennifer Burns was a member of the Arizona House of Representatives for three terms. She represented the 25th District, winning for the first time in November 2002. She won re-election in 2004 and 2006. She lost to Russell Jones during her unsuccessful re-election bid in 2008. Even though she was eligible to run in the 2008 election, she chose not to. ==References== Category:Arizona Republicans Category:Members of the Arizona House of Representatives Category:Living people Category:Women state legislators in Arizona Category:21st-century American politicians Category:21st-century American women politicians Category:Year of birth missing (living people)
